-- GE says considers selling its Polish unit Bank BPH
-- 
-- Wed Oct 15, 2014 11:39AM EDT
-- None



WARSAW, Oct 15 (Reuters) - General Electric Co <GE.N> is considering selling its Polish mid-tier unit Bank BPH <BPHP.WA>, BPH said in a statement on Wednesday.

Bank BPH said that General Electric, which owns nearly 90 percent of the bank's shares through three subsidiaries, has informed BPH that it is "analysing strategic possibilities" of selling the bank's shares. Bank BPH, Poland's 10-largest bank by assets, has a market capitalisation of $961 million.